## 📂 File & Directory Commands

```bash
pwd          # Show current directory
ls           # List files
ls -l        # Detailed list
ls -a        # Show hidden files

mkdir folder # Create directory
cd folder    # Change directory
cd ..        # Move back

touch file.txt   # Create file
rm file.txt      # Delete file
rm -r folder     # Delete directory
📝 File Handling
cat file.txt     # View file content
nano file.txt    # Edit file
less file.txt    # View large file
🔐 Permissions
ls -l              # Check permissions
chmod 777 file.txt # Full permissions
chmod 600 key.pem  # Secure file

Permission Types:

r → Read
w → Write
x → Execute
👤 User Commands
whoami     # Current user
sudo su    # Switch to root user
⚙️ Package Management (Ubuntu)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx
🔄 Process Management
ps -ef          # List processes
kill -9 <pid>   # Kill process
📜 Shell Scripting
📌 What is Shell Script?

A shell script is a file containing multiple Linux commands used to automate tasks.

✍️ Create Your First Script
touch script.sh
nano script.sh
Add Script:
#!/bin/bash

echo "Hello DevOps"
Run Script:
chmod +x script.sh
./script.sh
🔁 Variables
name="Chanti"
echo $name
🔀 Conditional Statements
#!/bin/bash

num=10

if [ $num -gt 5 ]
then
  echo "Greater"
else
  echo "Smaller"
fi
🔁 Loops
for i in 1 2 3 4
do
  echo $i
done
🧪 Real-Time DevOps Script
#!/bin/bash

echo "Updating system..."
sudo apt update

echo "Installing nginx..."
sudo apt install nginx -y

echo "Setup Complete!"
